28/08/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Defence Minister Ioan Mircea Pascu paid a one-day visit to Iraq on Tuesday (26 August) to experience the conditions faced by Romanian soldiers assigned to the international military mission there.
Radio Romania Actualitati reported Wednesday that the British and Polish commanders overseeing the Romanians praised their performance.
In other news, a German military delegation led by General Wolfgang Schneiderhan is to visit Bucharest on Thursday to discuss military reforms and bilateral co-operation.
(Rompres - 27/08/03)
